CM_ BO_ 712 "Jaguar/Land Rover HS-CAN message 0x2C8. Reverse engineered from X250/X351 captures. Observed ~15ms periodic rate. Associated with Dynamic Mode activation according to Canny 7.2 capture. Exact transmitter ECU and signal definitions unconfirmed.";

CM_ SG_ 712 JLR_2C8_Mode_State "Byte0. Appears to contain a state/multiplexer value on some vehicles. Observed values: 0xBF,0xC0,0xC1,0xC2,0xC3,0xC8,0xC9,0xCA,0xCB.";

CM_ SG_ 712 JLR_2C8_Status_Byte1 "Byte1. Changes correlated with Byte5 in captured datasets. Candidate mode/state field.";

CM_ SG_ 712 JLR_2C8_Config_Byte3 "Byte3. Constant 0xC5 in supplied capture. Function unknown.";

CM_ SG_ 712 JLR_2C8_State_LSB "Byte4. Used together with Byte5 in Canny Dynamic Mode detection logic (D5:D4 comparison).";

CM_ SG_ 712 JLR_2C8_State_MSB "Byte5. Used together with Byte4 in Canny Dynamic Mode detection logic. Suspected Dynamic Mode state byte.";

CM_ SG_ 712 JLR_2C8_Checksum_Alive "Byte7. Mostly constant (0xBD in supplied captures). Possible checksum/alive/status byte.";


